trailingComments.value: * * Delete a node n with one non-leaf left child and one leaf right * child. * * Precondition: * - n has exactly one non-leaf child. * - n is not the root * - n's only non-leaf child is n's left child. * - hence, n's right child is a leaf * - hence, n's left child is RED * - hence, n is BLACK * * @param {Node} n - The node to delete.
If n is black, deleting it reduces the black-height of every path going
We can easily fix this when its only child is an
internal RED node: change the color of the child to black and
